Copa Master Conmebol 1996

Played in Cuiabá, Brazil, Feb 8-12, 1996.

Participating clubs:

All winners of the Copa Conmebol 1992-1995.

Semifinals

São Paulo          7-3 Botafogo               [Feb 8]
  [Valdir 6' and 38', Almir 12', 31' and 55', Ailton 72', Edmilson 73';
   Tulio 33', 48' (pen) and 52'(pen)]
Atlético Mineiro   0-0 Rosario Central        [Feb 9, 10-9 on pen]


Final

São Paulo          3-0 Atlético Mineiro        [Feb 12]
  [Almir 9' and 51', Valdir 68']

Topscorer: Almir (São Paulo) 5 goals.

